<entry key="description">Currently, TableReader and TableWriter assume reading from and to a file. In fact, they must not assume anything about underlying data store and functions dealing with streams shall be removed.

Furthermore, AbstractTableReader and AbstractTableWriter shall be stripped down to general, common methods that most implementation will use. Two new abstract classes shall be created, AbstractStreamTableReader and AbstractStreamTableWriter, that deal with stream-based implementations.</entry>
